This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring October 24, 2010, as United Nations Day. The proclamation highlights the significance of the United Nations and its mission to promote peace, justice, and progress. It acknowledges the UN's role in addressing global challenges such as nuclear proliferation, climate change, terrorism, food security, and pandemic diseases. The proclamation also emphasizes the UN's efforts in providing humanitarian assistance, supporting education and development, and resolving conflicts. Obama urges the governors of all states in the United States to observe United Nations Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.